.TH TMUX-SAVE-SESSION 1 "2026-06-30" "tmux-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tmux-save-session \- save a tmux session layout as a restore script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tmux-save-session
.RB [ -d
.IR dir | --dir
.IR dir ]
.RI [ session-name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tmux-save-session
captures a tmux session's window names, pane layouts, pane working
directories, and active window into an executable restore script. When no
session name is supplied, the current tmux session is saved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI -d ", --dir " dir
Directory where restore scripts are written.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TMUX_TOOLS_SESSION_DIR
Default session directory. If unset, the default is
an absolute
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/tmux/sessions ,
then
.IR $HOME/.local/share/tmux/sessions .
Empty and relative XDG data paths are ignored. If neither base directory is
available, the command reports an error.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The session was saved.
.TP
.B 1
Unexpected shell failure.
.TP
.B 2
The command reported an error, such as invalid arguments, missing tmux context,
or an unreadable session.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmux-restore-session (1),
.BR tmux (1)
